<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,793,925]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
This is the only species of 
<taxonomicName box="[461,514,794,817]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[461,514,794,817]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Puto</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from the tropical areas of southern Asia, all other members of the genus occur in the Palaearctic, Nearctic and Neotropical Regions. It was collected at 
<number box="[1027,1083,829,853]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="2400.0">2400</number>
metres in humid forest in 
<collectingCountry name="Thailand" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. The tubular ducts on the frons of 
<taxonomicName box="[588,753,865,889]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Puto" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thailandicus">
<emphasis box="[588,753,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">P. thailandicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are about the same size as the other ventral ducts, which is a distinctive feature of the species.
</paragraph>
